### Swagat Odisha Backend API Tests
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tools

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@apiUrl = {{baseUrl}}/api

### 1. Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 2. Root Endpoint
GET {{baseUrl}}/

### 3. API Health Check
GET {{apiUrl}}/health

### 4. Test Endpoint
GET {{apiUrl}}/test

### 5. User Registration
POST {{apiUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "fullName": "Test User",
    "email": "testuser@example.com",
    "password": "testpassword123",
    "phoneNumber": "9876543210",
    "role": "student"
}

### 6. User Login
POST {{apiUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "testuser@example.com",
    "password": "testpassword123"
}

### 7. Create Test Application (No Auth Required)
POST {{apiUrl}}/student-application/create-test
Content-Type: application/json

### 8. Get Submitted Applications (Debug)
GET {{apiUrl}}/student-application/submitted-debug

### 9. Get Applications Count (Debug)
GET {{apiUrl}}/debug/applications-count

### 10. Get Document Statuses (Debug)
GET {{apiUrl}}/debug/document-statuses

### 11. CORS Test
OPTIONS {{apiUrl}}/auth/login
Origin: http://localhost:3000
Access-Control-Request-Method: POST
Access-Control-Request-Headers: Content-Type

### 12. Performance Metrics
GET {{apiUrl}}/performance/metrics

### 13. Performance Recommendations
GET {{apiUrl}}/performance/recommendations

### 14. Test with Authentication (Replace TOKEN with actual token from login)
# @token = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
# GET {{apiUrl}}/auth/profile
# Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 15. Test Student Applications with Auth
# GET {{apiUrl}}/student-application/my-application
# Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

